other_tests.findings: A sub-4 mm left lower lobe pulmonary nodule; hypodensities in the liver likely representing a cyst, hemangiomas; significant amount of stranding adjacent to the cecum and appendix; appendicolith at the origin of the appendix; markedly dilated appendix measuring 1.6 cm; wall discontinuity compatible with a perforation; small non-drainable fluid collection adjacent to the wall discontinuity representive of phlegmonous changes/developing early abscess.
